name: Brain
description:
Edward Weston was a prominent American photographer.
For Weston, it was as if the objects used in everyday experience had become living and living figures, forms that were both the expression and the reason for the inner life of objects. The thrilling visual power of Weston's work is the product of a deeper achievement: he freed his eyes from conventional and conventional expectation and taught them to see the expression of intention and meaning in the natural form.
And I made a collage in the shape of a brain with some of his works
